<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="321" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[159,772,1421,2018]" box="[159,298,1421,1447]" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis box="[159,298,1421,1447]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[159,772,1421,2018]" lastBlockId="9.[816,1429,795,923]" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">
A small leaf-nosed bat with a forearm length of 
<quantity box="[159,263,1488,1514]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.97" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" unit="mm" value="49.7">49.7 mm</quantity>
(
<tableCitation box="[276,367,1488,1514]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="7.[159,172,220,241]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="TABLE 2. External measurements (mm) and bacular length (mm) of 14 bat species recently collected at Lekoumou, Congo.Acronyms explained in the Materials and Methods section include means, ranges, and, where relevant, standard deviations. Numbers in parentheses refer to sample size where they differ from those stated in column 2" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5FAA6645FF93C07DFF03FF23FC6EFEEE" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" tableUuid="5FAA6645FF93C07DFF03FF23FC6EFEEE">Table 2</tableCitation>
). Apart from their smaller size, the external features, including the noseleaf, are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Noack" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[299,403,1555,1581]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[299,403,1555,1581]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">H. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described above. With a skull length of 
<quantity box="[270,389,1589,1615]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.813" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" unit="mm" value="18.13">18.13 mm</quantity>
(
<tableCitation box="[403,492,1589,1615]" captionStart="TABLE" captionStartId="8.[99,112,725,746]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="TABLE 3. Cranial and dental measurements (mm) of 14 bat species recently collected at Lekoumou, Congo.Acronyms explained in the Materials and Methods section include means, ranges, and, where relevant,standard deviations. Numbers in parentheses refer to sample size where they differ from those stated in column 2" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/5FAA6645FF9CC072FFFFFD2AFAA7FCC7" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" tableUuid="5FAA6645FF9CC072FFFFFD2AFAA7FCC7">Table 3</tableCitation>
) and an upper toothrow length (C–M 
<superScript attach="left" box="[310,320,1618,1636]" fontSize="8" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">3</superScript>
) of 
<quantity box="[370,478,1623,1649]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.18" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" unit="mm" value="6.18">6.18 mm</quantity>
, the skull is smaller than that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Noack" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[261,371,1656,1682]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[261,371,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">H. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The chambers of the rostrum appear similar in size, proportionately, to those of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Noack" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[159,262,1723,1749]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[159,262,1723,1749]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">H. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; this finding is in contrast to 
<bibRefCitation author="Kock" box="[620,771,1723,1749]" firstAuthor="Kock" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" pagination="1 - 238" refId="ref14130" refString="KOCK, D. 1969. Die Fledermaus-Fauna des Sudan (Mammalia, Chiroptera). Abhandlungen der Senckenbergischen Naturforschenden Gesellschaft, 521: 1 - 238." type="journal article" year="1969">Kock (1969)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Happold and Happold" box="[212,569,1757,1783]" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" refId="ref13898" refString="HAPPOLD, M., and D. C. D. HAPPOLD (eds.). 2013. Mammals of Africa Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews, and bats. Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book" year="2013">Happold and Happold (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. The frontal depression is very shallow and the well defined supraorbital ridges join the sagittal crest, which is less well developed than in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Noack" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[458,566,1858,1884]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[458,566,1858,1884]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">H. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, on the anterior part of the braincase. This is in contrast to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Noack" baseAuthorityYear="1893" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">H. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where they join in the mid-part of the constriction between the rostrum and the braincase. The dentition is comparable to that of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Noack" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[608,717,1992,2018]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[608,717,1992,2018]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">H. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but proportionately smaller (
<figureCitation box="[1106,1201,795,821]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="9.[159,172,652,673]" captionTargetBox="[371,1222,226,629]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[346,1234,218,637]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIG. 5. Lateral view of anterior skull and mandible of (A): Hipposideros caffer, HZM.244.40187, ♂ and (B): H. ruber, HZM.78.40176, ♂. Scale = 2 mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3943573" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3943573/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">Fig. 5A</figureCitation>
). The penis is long; no baculum was recovered from the single specimen examined — either it is absent or was so small as to be overlooked in the dissection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="321" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[816,1429,965,1093]" box="[816,1014,965,991]" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">
<emphasis box="[816,1014,965,991]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">Taxonomic notes</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[816,1429,965,1093]" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">
See 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Noack" baseAuthorityYear="1893" box="[909,1016,999,1025]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ruber">
<emphasis box="[909,1016,999,1025]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">H. ruber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(above). Following 
<bibRefCitation author="Happold and Happold" firstAuthor="Happold" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" refId="ref13898" refString="HAPPOLD, M., and D. C. D. HAPPOLD (eds.). 2013. Mammals of Africa Volume IV: Hedgehogs, shrews, and bats. Bloomsbury Publishing, London, 800 pp." type="book" year="2013">Happold and Happold (2013)</bibRefCitation>
, this specimen from southern 
<collectingCountry name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">Congo</collectingCountry>
is referred to 
<emphasis box="[1013,1211,1067,1093]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="321">
H. c. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[1078,1207,1067,1093]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Lissonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="321" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="angolensis">angolensis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
